<subSubSection lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="39" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="37.[189,1399,1411,2027]" lastBlockId="38.[189,1398,267,329]" lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="39" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
In their synonymy list for 
<taxonomicName authority=", Hayman et al. (1966: 38)" authorityName="Hayman" authorityPageNumber="38" authorityYear="1966" box="[495,953,1411,1438]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fumigatus">
<emphasis box="[495,521,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">R.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[528,644,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">fumigatus</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayman" box="[658,953,1411,1438]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref265860" refString="Hayman R. W., Misonne X. &amp; Verheyen W. N. 1966. The bats of the Congo and of Rwanda and Burundi. Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum voor Midden Afrika, Zoologische Wetenschappen, Ser. 8, 154: 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1966">
Hayman 
<emphasis box="[764,823,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">et al.</emphasis>
(1966: 38)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
include 
<taxonomicName authority="J. A. Allen, 1917" authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1917" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="abae">
<emphasis box="[1053,1201,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Rhinolophus</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[1209,1266,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">abae</emphasis>
J.A. 
<bibRefCitation author="Allen J. A." editor="Allen J. A. &amp; Lang H. &amp; Chapin J. P. The" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="405 - 478" part="37" refId="ref255503" refString="Allen J. A. 1917. Part I. Systematic List. In: Allen J. A., Lang H. &amp; Chapin J. P. The American Museum Congo Expedition Collection of Bats. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 37 (18): 405 - 478." title="Part I. Systematic List" type="journal article" volumeTitle="American Museum Congo Expedition Collection of Bats" year="1917">Allen, 1917</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and they refer to Koopman, who considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1917" box="[807,864,1448,1474]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="abae">
<emphasis box="[807,864,1448,1474]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">abae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be very close to 
<taxonomicName box="[1111,1227,1448,1474]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fumigatus">
<emphasis box="[1111,1227,1448,1474]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">fumigatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at the species level and indicated that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1917" box="[475,532,1485,1511]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="abae">
<emphasis box="[475,532,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">abae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might only be a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[904,1020,1485,1511]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fumigatus">
<emphasis box="[904,1020,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">fumigatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The records for these two taxa were grouped together in the text, but they still provided two separate maps: 36 for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1917" box="[1178,1268,1522,1548]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="abae">
<emphasis box="[1178,1268,1522,1548]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">R. abae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 40 for 
<taxonomicName box="[189,339,1559,1585]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fumigatus">
<emphasis box="[189,339,1559,1585]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">R. fumigatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These maps indicate that the two taxa occur in the northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1112,1176,1559,1585]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">RDC</collectingCountry>
. Further 
<taxonomicName box="[1283,1399,1559,1585]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fumigatus">
<emphasis box="[1283,1399,1559,1585]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">fumigatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
records were reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[533,629,1595,1621]" name="Rwanda" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
and the southern provinces of Tanganyika, Lualaba and Haut- Katanga. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayman" box="[303,557,1632,1659]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref265860" refString="Hayman R. W., Misonne X. &amp; Verheyen W. N. 1966. The bats of the Congo and of Rwanda and Burundi. Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum voor Midden Afrika, Zoologische Wetenschappen, Ser. 8, 154: 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1966">
Hayman 
<emphasis box="[411,471,1632,1658]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">et al.</emphasis>
(1966)
</bibRefCitation>
also reported a series from 
<quantity box="[891,966,1632,1658]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.4" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="km" value="74.0">74 km</quantity>
on the Banana-Boma Road (RMCA 20649, 20651 to 20653), but these were re-identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1852" box="[897,1144,1669,1695]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lobatus">
<emphasis box="[897,1144,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Rhinolophus lobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martin" authorityYear="1838" box="[1197,1320,1669,1695]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="landeri">
<emphasis box="[1197,1320,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">R. landeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; Wim Wendelen, pers. comm.). However, two other 
<taxonomicName box="[742,892,1706,1732]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fumigatus">
<emphasis box="[742,892,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">R. fumigatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens have surfaced from the Kongo Central Province (Thysville: RBINS 22428 and 22429). 
<bibRefCitation author="Cotterill &amp; Happold" box="[882,1294,1743,1769]" firstAuthor="Cotterill" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="329 - 331" refId="ref259099" refString="Cotterill F. P. D. &amp; Happold M. 2013 a. Rhinolophus fumigatus Ruppell's Horseshoe Bat. In: Happold M. &amp; Happold D. (eds) Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats: 329 - 331. Bloomsbury Publishing, London." type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="a">Cotterill &amp; Happold (2013a: 330)</bibRefCitation>
indicate that 
<taxonomicName box="[245,398,1780,1806]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fumigatus">
<emphasis box="[245,398,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">R. fumigatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits savanna areas (miombo and mopane woodlands in south-central Africa). Their distribution map shows a patchy covering of sub-Saharan Africa consisting of a number of red areas in West Africa, northeast Africa (including NE 
<collectingCountry box="[808,871,1853,1879]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">DRC</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[883,982,1853,1879]" name="Rwanda" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[993,1087,1853,1879]" name="Uganda" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Uganda</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1099,1176,1854,1880]" name="Kenya" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Kenya</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1232,1336,1853,1880]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
), and southwestern Africa (
<collectingCountry box="[444,532,1890,1916]" name="Angola" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Angola</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[593,696,1890,1917]" name="Namibia" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Namibia</collectingCountry>
) as well as a number of individual records in southeastern Africa (
<collectingCountry box="[277,371,1927,1953]" name="Zambia" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Zambia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[381,510,1927,1953]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[519,680,1927,1954]" name="Mozambique" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
). From the data in 
<bibRefCitation author="ACR" box="[886,1030,1927,1954]" firstAuthor="ACR" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refId="ref254905" refString="ACR. 2016. African Chiroptera Report. AfricanBats, Pretoria. Available from http: // www. africanbats. org / index. php / publications / africa-chiroptera-report [accessed 28 Sep. 2017]." type="url" year="2016">ACR (2016)</bibRefCitation>
we know that the distribution in southern Africa is more extensive than Cotterill &amp; Happold’s map suggests, and this probably might also be the case in West Africa. As such, our distribution map is more extensive, indicating that 
<taxonomicName box="[1251,1399,2001,2027]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fumigatus">
<emphasis box="[1251,1399,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">R. fumigatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs over the major part of sub-Saharan Africa, with the exception of the coastal areas in West Africa, the Central African forest region and extreme southern Africa.
</paragraph>
